<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Letter</div>
<div class="nbunit" id="7May1933"><font color="red">7 May 1933</font> <i>Letters III</i> (Paul L&eacute;on to Frank Budgen): I sent you by request a volume about dreams which I should like to have back however as I should like to read it myself &hellip; will send you &hellip; play by Andr&eacute; Obey &hellip; LOIRE, the chief character is Anna de la Loire and her five daughters &mdash; tributaries. You will find the resemblance very striking in many parts &hellip; If you will send me registered your chapter on W.i.P. it will be read and commented upon &hellip; As regards the Nausicaa chapter you will receive a ponderous volume of some six hundred large pages on the origin and history of what he chooses to call &lsquo;Le Manteau de Tanit&rsquo; </div>
